."},{"content":"Remove ice cream mixture from freezer and cut into cubes (4 cm). Add ice cream cubes and combine <b>30 sec\/speed 8<b>, or until well combined. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula."},{"content":"Add reserved fruit-almond mixture and combine <b>5 sec\/\/speed 5<b>."},{"content":"Transfer into a freezable pudding basin (18-20 cm, 1500 ml capacity) and return to the freezer for 1 hour. Stir with a spoon and ensure that the fruit and nuts are evenly distributed throughout the pudding. Place pudding basin into the freezer to set overnight."},{"content":"Place chocolate into mixing bowl and melt <b>2 min\/50°C\/speed 1<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula, then melt a further <b>1-2 min\/50°C\/speed 1<b>, or until melted."},{"content":"Remove ice cream from the freezer, then run the outside of the pudding basin under hot water for approx. 30 seconds. Place pudding basin upside down on a serving plate and carefully turn ice cream bombe out."},{"content":"Drizzle melted chocolate over the top of the pudding, allowing it to drizzle down the sides of the ice cream bombe. Place back into the freezer until chocolate has set (approx. 10 min). Slice ice cream bombe into wedges and serve immediately."}],"hintsAndTricks":["If you don't want to make an ice cream bombe you can cut it into wedges or scoop into ice cream cones and drizzle with chocolate instead."],"basicInfo":["easy","25m","48h 25m","8 portions"]}